"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967799","Department for Education","false","2018-09-12","<p>As at 31 March 2018, Ofsted inspection data shows the proportion of schools in Middlesbrough, Redcar and Cleveland:</p><p>a) There were 84% of schools in Middlesbrough classified as Good or Outstanding, and</p><p>b) There were 86% of schools in Redcar and Cleveland classified as Good or Outstanding.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-09-12T13:59:49.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967799/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967799/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967799/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-09-04","Schools: North Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of schools in (a) Middlesbrough and (b) Redcar and Cleveland are classified as Good or Outstanding by Ofsted.","false","Biography information for Mr Simon Clarke","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Mr Simon Clarke","170439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967800","Department for Education","false","2018-09-12","<p>Information on the proportion of pupils who achieved the English Baccalaureate in each year is published at local authority, regional and national level in the 'GCSE and equivalent results in England: statistical first release' series[1]; the English Baccalaureate was first available in 2009/10. The percentage of pupils, in state-funded schools, achieving the English Baccalaureate in each academic year is provided in the attached table.</p><p><br>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-gcses-key-stage-4" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-gcses-key-stage-4</a>.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-09-12T16:37:35.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967800/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967800/answer","170440_Percentage_Students_Achieving_EBacc.docx.pdf","170440_Percentage_Students_Achieving_EBacc","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967800/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-09-04","English Baccalaureate: North Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of children in (a) Middlesbrough and (b) Redcar and Cleveland achieved the English Baccalaureate attainment measure in each year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Mr Simon Clarke","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Mr Simon Clarke","170440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967801","Department for Education","false","2018-09-12","<p>The department publishes information on the percentage of 15 year old pupils from state-funded and special schools who entered higher education by age 19 by free school meal status, local authority and region. Figures for Middlesbrough, and Redcar and Cleveland can be found in Table 2a of the following file:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/635104/SFR39-2017-MainTables.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/635104/SFR39-2017-MainTables.xlsx</a>.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-09-12T08:39:04.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967801/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967801/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967801/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-09-04","Universities: North Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of (a) all pupils and (b) pupils from disadvantaged backgrounds in (i) Middlesbrough and (ii) Redcar and Cleveland entered university in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Mr Simon Clarke","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Mr Simon Clarke","170441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967802","Department for Education","false","2018-09-12","<p>The attached table shows figures for apprenticeship starts in the Middleborough South and East Cleveland constituency since the 2009/10 academic year, including data for the first three quarters of the 2017/2018 academic year (August 2017 to April 2018) as published in the FE data library: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fe-data-library" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fe-data-library</a>.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-09-12T14:32:10.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967802/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967802/answer","170442_Apprenticeship_starts_by_age_and_academic_ year.xls","170442_Apprenticeship_starts_by_age_and_year ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/967802/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-09-04","Apprentices: Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many young people in the Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland constituency started an apprenticeship in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Mr Simon Clarke","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Mr Simon Clarke","170442"
